      <div class="section-label">The asymptotic engine</div>
      <h2>What ExergyNet is becoming</h2>
      <p>
        Legacy settlement systems scale cost linearly with participation. Every worker,
        agent, or proof path adds more verification weight. ExergyNet LNES-03 changes
        the settlement geometry: child proofs generated across the swarm are folded into
        a parent aggregation path.
      </p>
      <p>
        The local LNES-03 prototype has validated the first recursive proof step:
        multiple child proofs can be consumed by a parent aggregator proof. That local
        recursion layer is the basis for a future BatchSettleExergy instruction, where
        the on-chain program consumes compressed commitments instead of inspecting every
        individual worker proof.
      </p>

